    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2024-02-06</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2024-03-01T21:17:21Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Supporting Treatment and Recovery Over Narcotics for Growth, Empowerment, and Rehabilitation Act or the STRONGER Act&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This bill revises and reauthorizes through FY2029 grants for residential substance use disorder treatment programs at state and local correctional and detention facilities.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Among the revisions, the bill&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;replaces statutory references to &lt;em&gt;substance abuse&lt;/em&gt; with &lt;em&gt;substance use disorder&lt;/em&gt;,&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;specifies that the term &lt;em&gt;residential substance use disorder treatment program&lt;/em&gt; includes a medication-assisted treatment program, &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;requires the chief medical officer or other staff overseeing a program to complete training on the science of addiction and the latest research and clinical guidance on treating substance use disorders in criminal justice settings, and&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;allows people who are awaiting trial or in pretrial detention to participate in the programs.&lt;br&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
